  "prompt": "What are the incarnations of lord Krishna in kaliyuga?",
  "response": "In Hindu tradition, Lord Vishnu is believed to incarnate in various forms, known as **avatars**, to restore cosmic order (dharma) whenever it is threatened by evil and chaos. These avatars are categorized into the **Dashavatara**\u2014the ten primary incarnations of Vishnu.\n\n### **Lord Krishna's Position in the Dashavatara**\n\n- **Lord Krishna** is recognized as the **eighth avatar** (**Ashtavatara**) of Lord Vishnu.\n- He manifested during the **Dvapara Yuga**, the third age in the cyclical concept of time, preceding the current epoch, the **Kali Yuga**.\n\n### **Incarnations in Kali Yuga**\n\n**Kali Yuga** is the fourth and final age in the cycle, characterized by decline in righteousness and an increase in vice. According to traditional Hindu scriptures, **only one major avatar of Vishnu is prophesied to appear during Kali Yuga**:\n\n- **Kalki**: Predicted to be the tenth and final avatar of Vishnu, Kalki is foretold to appear at the end of Kali Yuga. His mission will be to eradicate adharma (unrighteousness), restore dharma, and usher in a new cycle starting with Satya Yuga (the age of truth).\n\n### **Summary of Incarnations Relative to Kali Yuga**\n\n1. **Past Avatars** (prior to Kali Yuga):\n   - **Matsya** (Fish)\n   - **Kurma** (Turtle)\n   - **Varaha** (Boar)\n   - **Narasimha** (Man-Lion)\n   - **Vamana** (Dwarf)\n   - **Parashurama** (Warrior with an axe)\n   - **Rama** (Prince and King of Ayodhya)\n   - **Krishna** (Prince, statesman, and divine guide in the Mahabharata)\n\n2. **Present and Future Avatars**:\n   - **Buddha**: Some traditions include Buddha as the ninth avatar.\n   - **Kalki**: The prophesied tenth avatar set to appear in Kali Yuga's latter part.\n\n### **Other Beliefs and Interpretations**\n\nWhile the **Dashavatara** framework is widely accepted, various **sectarian traditions** within Hinduism may have additional beliefs or interpretations regarding divine manifestations in Kali Yuga. For instance:\n\n- **Guru or Spiritual Guides**: Many Hindu traditions believe that enlightened beings, gurus, and saints continue to guide humanity spiritually during Kali Yuga.\n- **Divine Presence**: Some believe that aspects of Krishna's divinity continue to influence and support devotees spiritually, even if He does not incarnate in a new physical form.\n\nHowever, **according to mainstream Hindu scriptures and traditional teachings**, **Kalki** remains the singular prophesied **incarnation** intended specifically for the challenges of Kali Yuga.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nIn summary, **during Kali Yuga**, **Kalki** is the **sole prophesied incarnation** of Lord Vishnu expected to appear to restore dharma. **Lord Krishna** himself, having incarnated in the preceding Dvapara Yuga, does not have a distinct reincarnation role in Kali Yuga according to traditional Hindu beliefs.\n\nIf you are exploring beliefs beyond the mainstream narratives, such as regional traditions or specific philosophical interpretations, there might be varied perspectives on divine manifestations in the current age. However, **Kalki** remains the central figure anticipated to fulfill this role in the broader Hindu framework.",
